      "span_text": "In addition, for time-gated acquisition, where the total imaging duration is equal to the product of the number of gates by the integration time per gate, a tradeoff between decay resolution (number of gates), signal-to-noise ratio (related to the integration time per gate) and total integration time, needs to be found in order to avoid excessive delay between the start and end of the acquisition. [CITATION_1]"
